WEBVTT

01:16.785 --> 01:19.037
IF WISHES COULD KILL

01:19.120 --> 01:19.996
Se-ah.

01:36.721 --> 01:38.098
I'll be all right.

01:38.640 --> 01:39.641
Soon.

01:54.531 --> 01:56.491
There was someone else in there too?

01:56.991 --> 01:57.992
Yeah.

01:58.993 --> 02:01.287
That's why I woke up so freaked out.

02:01.996 --> 02:04.833
The girl pointed
to someone who was behind me.

02:04.916 --> 02:08.419
So, it's possible
there's another entity involved?

02:09.129 --> 02:10.755
The yundo compass is in there?

02:14.509 --> 02:16.761
As long as you're wearing this,
they can't touch you.

02:16.845 --> 02:19.264
But if it comes off,
you get back here immediately.

02:19.347 --> 02:20.181
Okay.

02:20.265 --> 02:23.017
Also come back right away
if the timer starts going again.

02:25.395 --> 02:28.857
You'll have your phone with you,
but don't answer any calls or messages.

02:28.940 --> 02:32.152
I'll keep in touch
through Bangwool or Ha-joon.

02:33.069 --> 02:35.405
Do you always
have to go around barking orders?

02:38.283 --> 02:41.244
What I mean is try not to worry so much.

02:42.036 --> 02:43.705
You are kind of bossy.

02:44.956 --> 02:46.666
Which is a great quality.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.502
Take good care of these guys.

02:50.712 --> 02:53.715
You got it, boss. You kids are safe.
I'll look out for you.

02:53.798 --> 02:56.134
I won't let anyone
hurt a hair on your heads.

02:56.759 --> 02:57.677
We got this.

03:05.560 --> 03:06.561
See you later.

03:25.163 --> 03:26.998
What's wrong? Did you forget something?

03:28.249 --> 03:29.125
No.

03:29.876 --> 03:30.877
I wanted to say…

03:32.503 --> 03:34.130
…thanks for what you're doing.

03:35.006 --> 03:38.051
Take care of yourself while we're gone.
We really need our shaman.

03:53.816 --> 03:57.779
So, Ha-young can't step foot
off the property, is that it?

03:57.862 --> 03:59.072
Hm.

03:59.155 --> 04:00.907
Not if she wants to stay in one piece.

04:01.908 --> 04:03.952
There's a sort of protective energy
for her at home.

04:04.619 --> 04:06.579
Does she have cancer or something?

04:06.663 --> 04:10.583
No, Haetsal's healthy as a horse.
It's just complicated. Hmm.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.795
-She's trapped there?
-Hmm.

04:13.878 --> 04:17.215
Is that it? She'll have to spend
the rest of her life in that compound?

04:17.966 --> 04:19.050
That's the choice she made?

04:21.052 --> 04:24.389
I'll find a solution.
I'll get her back her freedom, I promise.

04:24.472 --> 04:27.725
I'll do whatever it takes
to fulfill her dream.

04:39.279 --> 04:42.323
GOODBYE
FROM SEORIN-SI

04:49.289 --> 04:50.456
Nice to see you.

04:52.417 --> 04:54.210
Looks like we'll be able
to check you out soon.

05:13.104 --> 05:13.938
Oh!

05:22.905 --> 05:24.991
Hey. What are you doing here?

05:25.825 --> 05:28.369
Se-ah's aunt needed me
to pick something up for her.

05:28.453 --> 05:29.829
They let you out?

05:29.912 --> 05:31.789
Let's not talk out here.

05:40.006 --> 05:44.177
REPAIR COMPLETE

05:50.266 --> 05:51.392
HAPPY BIRTHDAY

05:51.476 --> 05:53.603
Fix it as a present for my birthday?

05:53.686 --> 05:54.896
I told you, I can't.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.856
My old PIN is the new one. Thank you.

06:22.673 --> 06:23.841
Is this what spies do?

06:23.925 --> 06:25.802
I do feel like I'm spying on him.

06:25.885 --> 06:28.262
Hyeong-wook had to find out
about Girigo somehow,

06:28.346 --> 06:30.431
so I'm looking through
his messaging, browser history,

06:30.515 --> 06:33.643
system files, and caches to see exactly
how that thing got on his phone.

06:33.726 --> 06:35.895
Since it's synched to his Google account,

06:35.978 --> 06:39.816
we can also see what he searched
on his phone and what websites he went on.

06:39.899 --> 06:42.485
I won't pretend I understood all that,
but it'll take a while?

06:42.568 --> 06:44.028
Not at all. I'm almost done.

06:44.112 --> 06:45.655
I'm only looking at June 2nd.

06:46.614 --> 06:47.824
The test was on the 3rd.

06:48.574 --> 06:49.409
Mm.

06:50.034 --> 06:53.871
Hyeong-wook was so stressed about the exam
he was popping pills like candy.

06:53.955 --> 06:56.749
He was adamant about not wasting money
on in-game transactions.

06:56.833 --> 06:59.335
So whether he believed in Girigo or not,

06:59.419 --> 07:02.171
he would have wanted to know it if worked
before he even made a wish.

07:03.214 --> 07:04.048
Mm.

07:05.967 --> 07:10.012
There's nothing particular on June 2nd,
except that he was on Discord a lot.

07:10.096 --> 07:11.556
He played disco on his computer?

07:12.849 --> 07:13.891
Hm?

07:16.394 --> 07:18.187
Discord is a social media platform

07:18.271 --> 07:22.942
that combines screen sharing, messaging,
voice chat, and forums all into one.

07:23.818 --> 07:24.986
Oh!

07:25.903 --> 07:27.238
He's getting a call.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.408
Let's stay muted. But answer.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.247
Hyeong-wook! What the fuck?
I've been losing my shit 'cause of you.

07:36.330 --> 07:38.624
-Do you know this guy?
-Yo! Are you there?

07:38.708 --> 07:39.792
If you're gonna pick up,

07:39.876 --> 07:40.918
say something.

07:41.419 --> 07:42.420
Hello?

07:43.629 --> 07:44.714
Dude?

07:47.300 --> 07:49.010
This isn't Hyeong-wook, is it?

07:50.470 --> 07:51.554
Who are you?

07:52.638 --> 07:53.473
It's me!

07:55.099 --> 07:56.392
I got really bad strep.

07:58.227 --> 07:59.353
Oh. Um…

08:03.649 --> 08:07.695
Where are you? Study hall?
It's like you're obsessed. SNU or bust!

08:07.778 --> 08:10.948
You said you're losing your shit?
Why? What's up?

08:14.494 --> 08:18.873
What's up, dumbass, is that I heard
a crazy rumor that you offed yourself!

08:19.916 --> 08:21.417
Thank God it's a bunch of bull.

08:24.295 --> 08:25.588
Why's he so relieved?

08:28.299 --> 08:30.343
He knows exactly what Girigo is.

08:30.843 --> 08:31.761
Mm-hmm.

08:33.971 --> 08:35.515
So, is that why you're calling now?

08:35.598 --> 08:39.101
To see if all those rumors were true?
Did you think you were talking to a ghost?

08:39.185 --> 08:42.813
I don't believe in ghosts, idiot.
I called about the thing you asked for.

08:43.314 --> 08:46.067
I got it for you.
You still want it or not?

08:47.860 --> 08:49.529
Of course. Let's meet in an hour.

08:49.612 --> 08:50.738
Coffee shop?

08:56.536 --> 08:58.120
An hour?

09:03.543 --> 09:05.628
Okay. I don't get the rush,
but I'll be there.

09:05.711 --> 09:07.463
The usual place. Not a coffee shop.

09:08.089 --> 09:10.174
Oh no. You know what the usual is?

09:11.676 --> 09:13.010
We're toast?

09:15.888 --> 09:16.889
Are we toast?

09:20.434 --> 09:21.894
If this works, maybe not.

09:23.104 --> 09:25.731
We should be able
to track Hyeong-wook's movements

09:25.815 --> 09:27.441
that were registered on his phone.

09:30.403 --> 09:33.322
From what that guy said,
they have a regular meeting place.

09:33.406 --> 09:36.158
-It'll show up on here pretty often.
-Baekun Middle School?

09:53.759 --> 09:55.845
Can you move your feet?

09:57.972 --> 10:00.433
You do realize
that's the third time you've looked there?

10:00.516 --> 10:02.101
Your phone's not just gonna appear.

10:02.602 --> 10:05.021
You've looked everywhere.
It must've gotten lost.

10:05.980 --> 10:08.524
Can I just borrow yours a sec?

10:08.608 --> 10:11.277
My whole life is on my phone.
I don't want you up in my business.

10:11.360 --> 10:13.738
All I need
is the video of when I went nuts.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.991
It's possible it'll show us
what I did with my phone.

10:18.075 --> 10:19.577
Not cool.

10:21.412 --> 10:22.997
Using those puppy dog eyes like that.

10:23.080 --> 10:24.915
-But still no snooping.
-Mm.

10:51.442 --> 10:52.610
Se-ah.

11:04.413 --> 11:06.957
I don't have all day
to look for your stupid phone.

11:07.041 --> 11:08.167
I'm going home.

11:11.253 --> 11:13.255
We said an hour, didn't we?

11:14.006 --> 11:15.633
I can't stand tardiness.

11:16.884 --> 11:17.885
I'll summon him.

11:21.305 --> 11:22.723
Be here now!

11:24.308 --> 11:25.142
Not quite.

11:26.268 --> 11:27.895
Next one.

11:29.980 --> 11:31.148
Show your face!

11:33.234 --> 11:34.944
Ooh. That's gotta be our guy.

11:36.779 --> 11:39.448
-Wait here.
-You need to bring him back to us.

11:39.532 --> 11:41.075
-You know that.
-Mm-hmm.

11:47.331 --> 11:49.041
This is a bad idea.

11:49.917 --> 11:51.043
Really? You think so?

11:55.589 --> 11:58.509
I could swear they said
it was around here. It's gotta be.

12:03.222 --> 12:05.516
Huh. How can I not see it?

12:09.979 --> 12:11.313
I don't think they'd lie.

12:11.814 --> 12:12.982
I'm on to you!

12:13.774 --> 12:15.985
-I'm not falling for this shit.
-The bus route, did it--

12:16.068 --> 12:18.362
This is how the woman
who was supposed to marry my brother

12:18.446 --> 12:19.739
got recruited to a cult.

12:19.822 --> 12:21.282
They got her so friggin' brainwashed!

12:21.365 --> 12:24.660
Those bastards control everything
in her life, and it's all total bullshit.

12:27.621 --> 12:28.581
Ogre Min-soo, right?

12:28.664 --> 12:30.082
-Yeah, dude. No--
-Oh?

12:32.376 --> 12:33.836
You trying to punk me, kid?

12:36.756 --> 12:37.757
Oh?

12:40.718 --> 12:42.470
Oh?

12:42.553 --> 12:43.471
Stop!

12:45.473 --> 12:47.141
Kids, come on!

12:48.768 --> 12:50.227
Hey! Stop!

12:56.275 --> 12:58.152
I'm not joining no damn cult!

13:00.029 --> 13:02.406
Hey, kid! We just wanna talk to you!

13:04.325 --> 13:06.702
-Ha-joon, if you're too tired, wait here.
-Just go. I'm okay.

13:19.673 --> 13:21.717
Hey! We just wanna talk!

13:34.855 --> 13:35.898
Jesus!

13:39.443 --> 13:41.320
Wait! Why are you running away?

13:41.403 --> 13:44.740
-I'd rather die than listen to you!
-You shit.

13:47.117 --> 13:50.162
-Where'd Se-ah go?
-I'm not sure. I lost sight of her.

13:56.168 --> 13:57.169
Get lost!

14:00.798 --> 14:01.632
Hey!

14:08.472 --> 14:09.390
No.

14:11.600 --> 14:13.143
Oh! Oh!

14:35.291 --> 14:37.251
-Hey.
-Go away.

14:37.751 --> 14:40.629
-Go find your guru.
-Stop running. I mean it.

14:52.266 --> 14:53.267
Huh?

15:05.571 --> 15:07.448
Was that Se-ah?

15:07.531 --> 15:09.074
Come on. She needs us!

15:13.287 --> 15:15.122
That was brutal.

15:17.833 --> 15:18.709
Hey.

15:19.877 --> 15:22.671
-I told you to stop running.
-How'd you jump that?

15:23.339 --> 15:24.924
Who are you?

15:25.883 --> 15:28.761
-Do you go to Hyeong-wook's birthdays?
-What? Hyeong-wook's birthdays?

15:28.844 --> 15:32.014
-What the fuck? We're not eight.
-I'm guessing you two weren't very close.

15:36.810 --> 15:38.354
What did you do to my friend?

15:38.437 --> 15:40.898
I'm a true believer in equal rights.

15:40.981 --> 15:44.860
I'll hit girls and guys equally!
Like this, this and this! You got that?

15:44.944 --> 15:47.488
I asked you what happened
to Hyeong-wook, asshole!

15:50.991 --> 15:52.952
-Are you all right?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

15:53.035 --> 15:54.912
Did he hurt you?

15:54.995 --> 15:56.956
Se-ah! Where'd he go?

15:57.039 --> 16:00.084
-Right there.
-Is he knocked out? Did you do that?

16:00.167 --> 16:01.293
Of course not.

16:02.336 --> 16:03.212
Huh.

16:04.004 --> 16:07.299
Yeah. He'll be fine. Up and at 'em.

16:07.383 --> 16:08.842
If I had a cult,

16:09.802 --> 16:11.470
I wouldn't want you in it.

16:12.596 --> 16:13.472
Cool?

16:16.141 --> 16:19.103
So, Hyeong-wook asked you
to get these pills for him?

16:19.186 --> 16:20.020
Yeah.

16:21.772 --> 16:24.775
Those are the pills I take
once in a while to calm my nerves.

16:24.858 --> 16:28.112
Hyeong-wook was getting monster
heart palpitations from what he was taking

16:28.195 --> 16:31.407
so I put an extra order in for my stuff
'cause he wanted to try it out.

16:31.490 --> 16:33.117
Why'd you run away from me?

16:33.867 --> 16:38.038
You would've run away if an old guy was
giving off vibes like you were earlier.

16:38.122 --> 16:39.456
-I'm old?
-No, sir.

16:39.540 --> 16:42.418
You and Hyeong-wook,
you met through Discord?

16:43.460 --> 16:45.462
And you're the one
who told him about Girigo?

16:51.385 --> 16:52.886
Why would you do that?

16:54.013 --> 16:55.723
So he'd make a wish and die?

16:55.806 --> 16:57.850
We're the ones who answered your call.

17:00.060 --> 17:01.020
Instead of him.

17:03.480 --> 17:05.274
Because Hyeong-wook is dead.

17:08.235 --> 17:09.862
Don't pretend that you're sad!

17:10.362 --> 17:13.699
You knew what would happen when his wish
came true. That's why you were scared.

17:19.288 --> 17:22.916
We saw it at the same time.
It was all right there in the post.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.919
-Only he skipped over all the details.
-There was a post?

17:26.503 --> 17:28.255
Yeah, there was. It's on my phone.

17:30.799 --> 17:31.633
It's this…

17:35.262 --> 17:36.847
-It got deleted.
-When?

17:36.930 --> 17:39.433
-The main message has gone.
-Did you delete it?

17:39.516 --> 17:41.810
-Let me see that.
-I don't know what happened. It wasn't me.

17:46.857 --> 17:48.525
"Seorin High. A Ghost Story."

17:48.609 --> 17:49.735
That's his school.

17:51.445 --> 17:53.906
He thought it was really cool
it was something from Seorin High.

17:53.989 --> 17:57.242
We go there too. Did it say anything
about what happens when you get your wish?

18:01.538 --> 18:05.000
I can't tell you exactly
if it was mentioned in there or not, but--

18:06.668 --> 18:09.797
-Do you need a reminder?
-I don't remember the exact words!

18:09.880 --> 18:13.217
Hyeong-wook and I talked about
all sorts of other stuff, you know?

18:13.300 --> 18:15.427
It wasn't just about that stupid post.

18:15.511 --> 18:19.598
Sounds like you guys were good friends,
but we were buddies on Discord.

18:19.681 --> 18:23.519
He was the only friend I had on there.
That's why I was so worried.

18:26.063 --> 18:28.857
The post was deleted
because of a rule violation.

18:29.858 --> 18:31.860
That post included names and a photo.

18:31.944 --> 18:33.654
You're not allowed to do that.

18:33.737 --> 18:36.615
I remember, when I saw it,
the post had both in it.

18:36.698 --> 18:39.159
It was pretty risky,
'cause they're really strict.

18:39.243 --> 18:42.162
So it's not surprising it got deleted.

18:42.663 --> 18:44.581
No risks, no reward, right?

18:45.082 --> 18:46.750
Do you remember the names that were on it?

18:47.584 --> 18:49.086
Kwon Si-won, Do Hye-ryung.

18:49.169 --> 18:53.382
You just pop the names out like that
and still pretend you forgot the details?

18:53.465 --> 18:55.092
'Cause of the crazy shaman's daughter.

18:56.301 --> 18:58.679
Everyone who goes
to Baekun Middle School's heard of her.

18:59.263 --> 19:00.139
She's crazy?

19:00.222 --> 19:01.098
Yeah.

19:01.181 --> 19:02.891
You said there was a photo
that got deleted?

19:03.600 --> 19:05.018
If you're telling the truth,

19:05.102 --> 19:08.063
we should be able to find a cached image
in Hyeong-wook's laptop.

19:18.615 --> 19:20.576
-Next time--
-I thought you were a creepy cult guy.

19:20.659 --> 19:22.494
I found this in the cache. Is this it?

19:23.996 --> 19:25.080
That's it.

19:25.581 --> 19:28.959
Si-won's on the left, and Hye-ryung
the shaman's daughter's on the right.

19:30.711 --> 19:32.379
KANG HA-YOUNG

19:32.462 --> 19:33.964
FILE TRANSFER

19:37.426 --> 19:39.428
-Oh!
-Whoa, what's with you?

19:40.470 --> 19:41.680
Where's the shaman's house?

19:44.224 --> 19:46.935
Your whole school knows
about the daughter. I want an address.

19:47.769 --> 19:49.104
I know the neighborhood.

19:51.815 --> 19:54.193
As soon as I get home,
I'm calling the police!

19:59.239 --> 20:01.867
It took a while,
but he was telling the truth.

20:01.950 --> 20:04.995
Se-ah, do you think these girls
could be the ones you saw?

20:05.078 --> 20:06.455
Yes.

20:06.538 --> 20:10.375
I didn't get a proper look at either
in my dream. But I know there were two.

20:10.959 --> 20:13.378
We're gonna try to find the house
where Do Hye-ryung lived.

20:13.462 --> 20:18.008
We should be there shortly. I'll check in
with you later if we find anything. Okay?

20:18.091 --> 20:21.428
-Okay. You guys be careful.
-We will. Don't worry.

20:34.441 --> 20:37.402
Why would ghosts
go out of their way to come here?

21:09.768 --> 21:11.728
Mm-hmm. Here.

21:12.229 --> 21:13.313
Let me show you.

21:13.397 --> 21:16.692
A shaman's house is marked
with symbolic flags on the outside,

21:16.775 --> 21:19.611
on the gates, or up above,
so people can see.

21:20.362 --> 21:23.031
-So you'll have to look up.
-Mm.

21:23.615 --> 21:26.994
I want you guys to stick close.
Whatever happens, don't go in alone.

21:27.077 --> 21:29.454
You call me if you find one. Hm?

21:29.538 --> 21:30.706
-Sure.
-Mm.

21:32.291 --> 21:33.292
Let's go.

21:37.296 --> 21:38.463
I say that way.

21:44.636 --> 21:46.096
Mm. This way.

21:47.139 --> 21:49.933
-Through here.
-How do you know it's this way?

21:52.060 --> 21:53.770
Do you know where you're going?

21:54.980 --> 21:57.190
It's gonna be dark before we get up there.

21:57.274 --> 21:59.359
Shouldn't we have a plan
before we go any further?

21:59.985 --> 22:04.239
-We can slow down if you need.
-It's not 'cause I'm out of breath.

22:04.323 --> 22:07.617
I just think it's not a good idea
to be searching once the sun goes down.

22:08.201 --> 22:10.329
Maybe we should split up
so it goes faster?

22:10.412 --> 22:13.081
It's actually gonna be easier
to see from up there once the sun sets.

22:13.665 --> 22:14.958
No, it won't.

22:15.042 --> 22:17.085
Trust me when it comes to this stuff.

22:17.169 --> 22:18.211
Let's go!

22:18.295 --> 22:20.505
-Quit stalling!
-Okay, get off me!

22:22.382 --> 22:23.508
You got this!

22:23.592 --> 22:24.551
Come on!

22:39.399 --> 22:40.525
-Look.
-Huh?

22:40.609 --> 22:42.319
That light's brighter than the others.

22:43.111 --> 22:44.196
Okay. Let's check.

22:44.863 --> 22:45.697
Hm.

22:47.199 --> 22:49.034
CORNER STORE

22:49.117 --> 22:51.286
Hello? Is anyone here?

22:52.913 --> 22:54.373
Are you still open?

22:57.876 --> 22:59.586
I guess you were sleeping. Sorry.

22:59.669 --> 23:01.922
How many times do I have to tell you?
I'm not leaving.

23:02.005 --> 23:05.467
-I don't think we've ever spoken.
-Sick of you punks bothering me.

23:05.550 --> 23:06.593
Hey.

23:07.761 --> 23:10.138
-Good evening. How are you, ma'am?
-Hello, ma'am.

23:10.222 --> 23:11.723
You must think I'm rude.

23:12.224 --> 23:15.185
I thought you were one of those thugs
from the looks of you.

23:16.728 --> 23:18.897
I guess you're used
to handsome thugs, then.

23:18.980 --> 23:22.109
You must be thirsty.
Get the expensive stuff as a reward.

23:22.859 --> 23:23.944
Oh, thanks.

23:24.778 --> 23:26.113
You can get more than one.

23:27.697 --> 23:29.741
Not those. That's the cheap stuff.

23:29.825 --> 23:31.451
The fancy ones are on the shelf.

23:31.535 --> 23:35.372
And the salt too.
Just buy all that stuff over there.

23:35.455 --> 23:38.375
-We'll take it all.
-Am I ever glad you came in.

23:39.376 --> 23:41.503
There's a great shaman
who lived in this neighborhood

23:41.586 --> 23:43.797
with their daughter,
and we need directions.

23:45.340 --> 23:46.591
Let's see.

23:46.675 --> 23:49.261
Ah! She did have a reputation.

23:49.344 --> 23:52.431
Only I'd describe her
as more of a quack really.

23:53.306 --> 23:56.143
-Do you know where her house is?
-Sure. We all do.

23:56.226 --> 23:59.479
You go out to the left,
and keep going straight

23:59.563 --> 24:01.273
until you see the green gate.

24:01.898 --> 24:03.817
Are you classmates with her daughter?

24:06.695 --> 24:07.529
We, uh…

24:08.155 --> 24:11.741
Mm. Now that I think of it,
I haven't seen her in three years or so.

24:15.245 --> 24:17.873
Could you tell me if this is
the shaman's daughter in the picture?

24:17.956 --> 24:19.791
Oh, yes. That's her.

24:20.459 --> 24:22.586
Now, what was her name again?

24:22.669 --> 24:23.670
Hye-ryung.

24:23.753 --> 24:25.005
Do Hye-ryung.

24:25.088 --> 24:26.298
Oh no.

24:26.381 --> 24:27.841
That's too unusual.

24:27.924 --> 24:30.302
I can't tell you what it was,
but it's not that.

24:30.385 --> 24:32.846
-Her name is just regular.
-What?

24:34.764 --> 24:38.059
This is the shaman's daughter,
only that's not her name.

24:41.855 --> 24:45.609
So the shaman's daughter isn't this girl?
It's this girl?

24:45.692 --> 24:47.486
The one on the left. That's her.

24:52.449 --> 24:53.325
Oh.

24:59.706 --> 25:00.749
Good night, ma'am.

25:03.418 --> 25:05.295
-Bangwool.
-Hm?

25:05.795 --> 25:08.381
I can give her back the salt now, can't I?

25:08.465 --> 25:11.176
-There's a reason I wanted that whole bag.
-Oh.

25:11.259 --> 25:13.094
Besides, it's the good stuff.

25:15.680 --> 25:17.516
Nice and snug. Let's go.

25:18.016 --> 25:20.185
-She said left, didn't she?
-Yep.

25:28.276 --> 25:30.070
-Look! Down there!
-Flags!

25:38.370 --> 25:41.414
Hm. We can't pick it, so…

25:50.674 --> 25:51.675
Wait here.

26:08.858 --> 26:09.818
We're good!

26:23.498 --> 26:26.251
This place doesn't make any sense.
Can you hand me that?

26:26.334 --> 26:27.210
Here.

26:28.378 --> 26:30.255
This is a dangganjiju.

26:30.338 --> 26:33.174
It's for setting up ceremonial flags
at Buddhist temples.

26:33.258 --> 26:34.843
It doesn't belong here at all.

26:35.510 --> 26:37.178
And there's blood on it.

26:40.640 --> 26:42.142
She wasn't a shaman.

26:43.101 --> 26:44.227
Or a ritual master.

26:45.228 --> 26:46.605
What the hell?

26:54.237 --> 26:55.238
Hold on.

26:56.489 --> 26:57.490
Don't move.

27:11.463 --> 27:12.589
-Stay there!
-Jesus Christ!

27:13.173 --> 27:14.132
Scoot together.

27:14.758 --> 27:16.551
-What?
-Scoot together.

27:16.635 --> 27:17.886
Closer?

27:22.515 --> 27:26.353
-Why so close?
-I'll tell you in a sec. Just stand still.

27:35.570 --> 27:37.113
I'm creating a protective field.

27:38.740 --> 27:40.241
To keep the evil spirits

27:40.325 --> 27:41.576
from possessing you.

27:50.627 --> 27:51.670
Squeeze together.

27:51.753 --> 27:53.254
It needs to be tight.

27:53.338 --> 27:55.590
And do not step outside this circle.

27:57.384 --> 27:59.552
Bangwool, it's still so hot.

28:00.345 --> 28:02.305
Do you really have to make it so tight?

28:02.389 --> 28:06.059
Mm-hmm. Because the tighter you make it,
the better it works.

28:07.018 --> 28:07.936
Oh.

28:11.606 --> 28:12.482
Now,

28:13.858 --> 28:17.445
if I yell for you to get out of here,
or if I'm not back in ten minutes,

28:17.529 --> 28:19.572
you run back to the car and get in.

28:21.408 --> 28:22.826
Lock yourselves inside,

28:22.909 --> 28:25.704
call Haetsal, and tell her
what's going on, on speakerphone.

28:27.038 --> 28:29.165
Stay in the car until sunrise. Got it?

28:29.249 --> 28:30.792
-Huh.
-Got it.

28:33.002 --> 28:34.045
Holy shit.

28:34.129 --> 28:37.132
What is it?!

28:37.215 --> 28:39.718
-You stayed inside. Good job, guys.
-I hate you.

28:43.930 --> 28:45.557
What if something comes after us?

28:46.641 --> 28:47.851
Stand still and yell.

28:47.934 --> 28:49.060
Loudly.

29:14.836 --> 29:16.379
It's crazy humid up here.

29:16.463 --> 29:17.422
Right?

29:18.798 --> 29:20.592
Uh-huh. Crazy.

29:25.096 --> 29:25.972
Hm.

29:54.959 --> 29:56.085
Is that blood?

30:09.557 --> 30:10.809
How long has it been?

30:14.979 --> 30:16.856
Almost three minutes.

30:16.940 --> 30:20.360
I can feel my sweat trickling.
It's really annoying.

30:21.110 --> 30:22.028
You?

30:22.111 --> 30:23.238
Yeah, a little.

30:23.738 --> 30:24.989
It's pretty gross.

30:35.166 --> 30:36.835
There's no shrine.

30:39.045 --> 30:40.004
Se-ah.

30:40.880 --> 30:41.881
What?

30:43.049 --> 30:44.050
Don't move an inch.

30:47.846 --> 30:49.514
Why? What's wrong?

30:53.560 --> 30:54.394
Sorry.

31:00.859 --> 31:03.820
Ow! What the hell?

31:03.903 --> 31:06.447
There was a mosquito.
I wanted to get it before it bit you.

31:11.870 --> 31:12.912
Ha-joon.

31:15.874 --> 31:16.958
Do you

31:18.001 --> 31:19.252
see that too?

31:20.712 --> 31:21.588
What?

33:34.429 --> 33:35.430
What are you doing?

33:36.305 --> 33:37.223
Se-ah, don't!

33:38.057 --> 33:39.017
Se-ah!

33:55.033 --> 33:56.743
A diorama of hell in a shrine?

33:59.662 --> 34:00.496
Huh?

34:04.751 --> 34:06.878
This is some spooky shit.

34:18.931 --> 34:20.725
What's she protecting with this?

34:38.242 --> 34:39.243
No.

34:39.952 --> 34:40.953
A deolmi?

34:42.997 --> 34:44.082
Is this a curse?

34:48.586 --> 34:50.505
Is that a cupboard or a door?

35:10.483 --> 35:11.484
That got me good.

35:17.698 --> 35:18.825
Ha-joon…

35:22.286 --> 35:23.996
do you see it? Right there?

35:26.666 --> 35:27.583
What?

35:36.467 --> 35:38.636
I think your mind's playing tricks on you.

36:11.752 --> 36:13.045
We should go back.

36:41.741 --> 36:43.034
Our school?

36:55.421 --> 36:56.672
Bangwool!

37:02.678 --> 37:03.596
Hey!

37:04.388 --> 37:07.850
Why'd you leave the circle?
I told you not to move, didn't I?

37:07.934 --> 37:11.646
The girl from my dream was here. She led
me to a place where this was buried.

37:20.112 --> 37:22.198
This wasn't the work of one person.

37:23.783 --> 37:26.369
The Buddhist influence
and the shamanic shrine look connected.

37:27.036 --> 37:30.122
But the other stuff,
it doesn't make sense.

37:30.206 --> 37:32.333
The sabotage in the shrine
and the diorama.

37:32.416 --> 37:36.379
It's hard to tell if they were trying
to protect someone or put a curse on them.

37:36.921 --> 37:38.673
The shop owner told you the shaman died?

37:38.756 --> 37:41.801
She happened to see her
get carted off for her burial rites.

37:41.884 --> 37:44.345
Would it make sense
to look into what kind of shaman she was?

37:44.428 --> 37:47.181
I think it would be better
to focus on the phone.

37:47.807 --> 37:51.602
I can see a window from the place
where Se-ah was taken on the other side.

37:52.186 --> 37:54.438
I think they made a video there,
so the red phone

37:54.522 --> 37:56.565
that turned into a maehyung must be there.

37:56.649 --> 37:57.525
Mm-hmm.

37:58.234 --> 38:00.486
Haetsal, please try not to get worked up.

38:01.112 --> 38:02.321
I'll find it somehow.

38:07.910 --> 38:09.370
Needle in a haystack.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.377
Too bad this picture isn't digital.

38:17.586 --> 38:20.131
-Why?
-Then we'd have location data.

38:21.132 --> 38:21.966
Wait.

38:22.675 --> 38:23.801
It's also in the videos.

38:24.844 --> 38:26.721
-Can you hold on to this?
-Yeah, sure.

38:27.263 --> 38:28.264
It's on there?

38:31.767 --> 38:34.478
This is the metadata
of Geon-woo's wish-making video.

38:36.897 --> 38:39.483
You see these numbers?
That's the GPS data.

38:39.567 --> 38:42.903
If you input that, it'll show you
the location where the video was made.

38:42.987 --> 38:47.158
And from what I can tell, Girigo videos
load in their original format.

38:47.241 --> 38:51.245
So that means if we get the video off
the server, the GPS data will be on there?

38:51.329 --> 38:53.122
-Mm.
-Whoa.

38:53.706 --> 38:56.125
Nerds could rule the world. You're good.

39:00.379 --> 39:02.882
It won't let me log in unless
I'm registered to the server though.

39:03.632 --> 39:06.093
Wait! This login looks familiar.

39:06.177 --> 39:07.261
Huh?

39:08.054 --> 39:09.096
You've seen it?

39:11.891 --> 39:13.934
ADMIN ID
4BONG

39:14.018 --> 39:15.561
On my coach's computer.

39:35.247 --> 39:37.792
-Is anyone there?
-Just Coach.

39:38.376 --> 39:39.377
That's her car.

39:39.460 --> 39:43.297
She usually comes out about now.
But she's almost always the last one here.

39:43.381 --> 39:46.050
So the coast will be clear
once she leaves the parking lot?

39:46.133 --> 39:47.009
Yeah.

39:47.093 --> 39:49.303
-Security cameras?
-I know a way around them.

39:50.513 --> 39:51.389
Hm.

39:51.889 --> 39:52.890
Se-ah.

39:53.724 --> 39:55.184
The ghost you saw at the house,

39:55.267 --> 39:57.853
would you be able to recognize
which of the two it was?

39:59.021 --> 40:02.733
Sorry. I don't know who she is,
but I think she wants to help me.

40:03.234 --> 40:04.443
She guided us to the picture.

40:09.824 --> 40:11.784
Don't jump to conclusions about her.

40:12.618 --> 40:15.079
She could be luring you in
with her deception.

40:15.162 --> 40:17.081
Ghosts are tricky creatures.

40:17.164 --> 40:19.375
Then maybe we should
have a countermeasure?

40:19.959 --> 40:21.168
We already have two.

40:21.252 --> 40:22.420
Me and your sister.

40:23.838 --> 40:25.840
Don't let your confidence
be the end of us.

40:27.258 --> 40:29.385
Oh. Ha-joon.

40:29.885 --> 40:31.512
We can go now. She's leaving.

40:31.595 --> 40:33.597
-Mm.
-Just the two of you?

40:35.516 --> 40:37.810
It's our school. We know our way around.

40:37.893 --> 40:39.645
And we won't look so suspicious.

40:39.728 --> 40:41.063
That makes sense.

40:46.318 --> 40:48.654
Good to go. But be careful.

40:48.737 --> 40:49.738
We will.

40:50.531 --> 40:52.533
-Stick together.
-We will.

41:13.929 --> 41:16.265
How did you know
there was a hole in the fence back here?

41:17.266 --> 41:19.393
-Because I'm the one who made it.
-Why?

41:19.477 --> 41:20.769
Stealth workouts.

41:21.270 --> 41:23.939
I got on the national team
with secret sessions.

41:24.607 --> 41:25.566
Huh.

41:26.984 --> 41:28.027
Ready?

41:28.110 --> 41:29.153
Yeah.

41:36.827 --> 41:38.078
One, two, three, four.

41:39.079 --> 41:41.040
-That's her security code?
-Mm-hmm.

41:41.123 --> 41:44.752
She thinks cybersecurity's a dirty word.
It's her code for everything.

41:49.381 --> 41:50.508
ADMIN ID: 4BONG
PASSWORD:

41:50.591 --> 41:51.926
One, two, three, four.

41:53.594 --> 41:55.387
Thanks, Coach Song.

41:56.514 --> 41:58.599
YOUTH APP DEVELOPMENT CONTEST
GIRIGO

41:59.934 --> 42:01.185
GIRIGO/VIDEO

42:04.396 --> 42:06.482
-Oh my God!
-What?

42:07.816 --> 42:08.734
Are there

42:09.860 --> 42:11.695
only videos from people who made wishes?

42:13.906 --> 42:14.782
Mm-hmm.

42:16.116 --> 42:17.201
That means…

42:19.245 --> 42:21.747
that's a wish video, right?

42:30.422 --> 42:34.843
There are two people
I want to be dead after this.

42:34.927 --> 42:36.220
NOVEMBER 4, 2008
LIM NA-RI

42:36.303 --> 42:38.973
Number one, that loser, Choi Hyeong-wook.

42:39.056 --> 42:40.641
Kinda goes without saying.

42:44.144 --> 42:45.604
Na-ri made a wish.

43:02.705 --> 43:04.582
Geon-woo, wait a sec.

43:08.961 --> 43:09.920
But then,

43:10.796 --> 43:12.256
how can she still be alive?
